$*INIT-INSTANT
constant dynamic
when Raku was started
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*INIT-INSTANT
The C<Instant> the raku process was started.

$*PROGRAM-NAME
variable dynamic string
name of current Raku program
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*PROGRAM-NAME
A string presentation of the path of the currently executing Raku
program.

$*PROGRAM
constant dynamic
current Raku program
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*PROGRAM
An C<IO::Path> of the currently executing Raku program.  Available at
compile time, and can thus be used as part of a C<use lib> statement.
=begin code :lang<raku>
use lib $*PROGRAM.sibling("lib");
=end code

$*EXECUTABLE-NAME
constant dynamic string
basename of the currently running Raku runtime
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*EXECUTABLE-NAME
A string presentation of the basename of the currently executing
Raku program (usually "raku" or "rakudo").

$*EXECUTABLE
constant dynamic
currently running Raku runtime
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*EXECUTABLE
An C<IO::Path> of the currently running Raku executable (typically
"rakudo").  Can be used as the initial argument to e.g. C<run>.

$*REPO
constant dynamic
start of repository chain
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*REPO
The first of a chain of C<CompUnit::Repository> objects that are
responsible for registering modules and making them available for
usage.

$*RAKU
constant dynamic
information on this Raku
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*RAKU
A C<Raku> object that contains information about the currently
executing version of the Raku Programming Language.

$*THREAD
constant dynamic
the current thread
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*THREAD
The C<Thread> object describing the currently active thread.

$*SCHEDULER
variable dynamic
the logic for scheduling the running of async work
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*SCHEDULER
The C<Scheduler> object that handles all scheduling of async jobs.

$*SAMPLER
variable dynamic
the current C<Telemetry> sampler
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*SAMPLER
The sampler logic for making snapshots of the system state.  Only
available if the C<Telemetry> module has been loaded.


contains all dynamic variables that respresent some type if internal
state of the runtime.  Even though they can be changed or shadowed,
it is usually a bad design decision to do so.
